result.description:
"The deliverable ""Vertical experts meetups sessions report 3"" will report the results of the 4 sessions of this task held between months 14  and 18  and in particular:
1) the upoload of the four TWIST webinars on the TWIST youtube channel;
2) PPT and documents related to the topic of the meetup and feedback from partecipating startups."

Starting from the elements defioned in the initial Dissemination plan, the Mid Term Dissemination plan will:
- report the results of the implemented actions; 
- verify the qualitative indicators;
- describe critical bottlenecks;
-  identify corrective actions.

The objective of this workpackage is to aggregate the TWIST community of ecosystem stakeholders. 
The community will have the opportunity to consider, discuss, propose and contribute to the definition, structure and optimal organizationm and future needs of the startup ecosystems
In order to achieve this objective, in the first two months of the project, each ecosystem will organize  a local event with the purpose of:
- presenting TWIST DIGITAL and future activities;
- definingTWIST platform functionalities and on line services;
- involving coaches and mentors;
- understanding startups need and wishes. 
The report will include all the experiences of each local events and inputs of stakeholders.
Sviluppo Lazio,as workpackage leader, in cooperation with LUISS ENLABS, Euratechnologies, Seedcap e Metapolska will elaborate a feasibility study for the implementation of the TWIST Platform.

"The deliverable ""Vertical experts meetups sessions report 2"" will report the results of the 4 sessions of this task held between months 12 and 18  and in particular:
1) the upoload of the four TWIST webinars on the TWIST youtube channel;
2) PPT and documents related to the topic of the meetup and feedback from partecipating startups."

Developing a dissemination plan is a key part of the collaborative activity of the TWIST and  can help TWIST team to focus the key objectives and identify key audiences in all the phases of the project.
The Dissemination plan will provide an effective list of the key elements that will be considered durin the whole duration of the project. 
This initial identification of key elements offers a good overview of some of 
the most critical things that should be considered and will be revised according to the merging needs of the project:
1) Dissemination goals;
2) target audience;
3)  Key message;
4)  Dissemination activities, tools, timing, and responsibilities;
5) Quality Indicators;
6) budget.

Twenty web startups will be selected to participate to the TWIST exchange program.
Each ecosystem will launch an open call to host one/two startups coming from the TWIST ecosystem.
The startups involved into the exchange program will have the opportunity to participate to the Challange of the ecosystem and will have the chance of working and living in a a different but complementary context.
This deliverable will report:
1) 4 TWIST exchange program open calls;
2) list, contact details and short description of webstartups applying to each call;
3) selection methodology;
4) Ranking of web startups;
5) feedback and results of the exchange program.
